Program: Outlook
Title: 05/10/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00kg6l4
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 6 Oct 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the US storm chaser who says he's intercepted more twisters than anyone else - on what it's like to be inside a tornado. Also, five years after Russian journalist Anna Politkovskaya was killed, her sister describes how her family coped with her loss. And the identical twins with three double lung transplants between them on their battle to raise organ donation rates in Japan. Show less